message.content:
cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.NI, cs.CY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses recent developments in relay attacks on contactless smartcards and secure elements, and proposes a real-world application of these attacks on the Google Wallet. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the components and results of a successful attempt to relay an EMV Mag-Stripe transaction between a Google Wallet device and an external card emulator over a wireless network. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of wireless networks in the relay attack on the Google Wallet. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the implications of these attacks on the security and privacy of users' financial information. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is the least likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the use of multimedia components (i.e. contactless smartcards) in the relay attack.
